A Deployment is high level obstraction that manages replicaset and pod 
The key features of deployment is Rolling updaes - meaning we already have an application running with V1   having 10 copies 
Now we want to Rollout (update or launch) V2 
What happends in Rolling update , it will not recreate all 10 at once This causes downtime rather 
its going to gradually update all the pods running inside the kubernetes cluster for the specific deployment 

with the help of rolling update we achive zero downtime deployments 
That feature is part of deployment objects and also easy Rollback , if something goes wrong in the deployment with simeple 
command # kubectl rollout undo <deployment-name> , we can easily rollback to its previouse stable version.

# kubectl create deployment nginx --image=nginx:latest --replicas=3 --dry-run=client -o yaml > nginx-deployment.yaml

# kubectl create -f nginx-deployment.yaml  ( Create )
# kubectl apply -f nginx-deployment.yaml ( Create or Update ) 

